class_description:
You typically use instances of NSUnitConcentrationMass to represent specific quantities of concentration using the NSMeasurement class.
Concentration is the abundance of a constituent within a volume. Concentration can be expressed by SI derived units in terms of kilograms per cubic meter (kg/m3).
The NSUnitConcentrationMass class defines its base unit as gramsPerLiter, and provides the following units, which are initialized using UnitConverterLinear converters with the specified coefficients:

params.param_description: The mass, in grams, for a mole of a given constituent.

return_description: A unit expressing millimoles per liter with the specified molar mass.

Methods.method_description: Returns the millmoles per liter unit with the specified number of grams per mole.
Methods.method_declar: class func millimolesPerLiter(withGramsPerMole gramsPerMole: Double) -> UnitConcentrationMass

Vars.var_description: Returns the grams per liter unit of concentration.
Returns the milligrams per deciliter unit of concentration.
